def: Of or pertaining to an accessory; as, accessorial agency,accessorial guilt.
Naturally growing in groups or masses; -- said of manyindividual plants of the same species.
To cover with, or as with, a canopy. "A bank with ivycanopied." Milton.
Involving surds; not capable of being expressed in rationalnumbers; radical; irrational; as, a surd expression or quantity; asurd number.
An organ for aquatic respiration; a branchia.Fishes perform respiration under water by the gills. Ray.
A low, mean wretch [Written also rascalion.]
Manner; custom; fashion; humor. [Prov. Eng.] [Written alsofarand.] Grose.
